                                          CcddTableTypeEditorHandler updatedEditor,
                                          java.lang.String[] tableNames)
        Perform the steps needed following execution of table type modification

        tableNames - array of modified table names

      • initialize

        private void initialize(java.lang.String[] typeNames)
        Create the table type editor dialog. This is executed in a separate thread since it can take a noticeable amount time to complete, and by using a separate thread the GUI is allowed to continue to update. The GUI menu commands, however, are disabled until the telemetry scheduler initialization completes execution
        Parameters:
        typeNames - array containing the table type names

      • getOverwriteFieldType

        private CcddConstants.OverwriteFieldValueType getOverwriteFieldType()
        Get the selected field value overwrite action
        Returns:
        OverwriteFieldValueType: ALL to overwrite all field values, SAME to overwrite only those fields with a matching value, EMPTY to overwrite only fields with blank values, or NONE to not overwrite any field values

      • storeAllChanges

        private void storeAllChanges()
        Commit changes to the database for every table in the editor that has changes. This command is executed in a separate thread since it can take a noticeable amount time to complete, and by using a separate thread the GUI is allowed to continue to update. The GUI menu commands, however, are disabled until the database command completes execution
